es to achieve common goals. With strong communication skills, you effectively engage with colleagues, promoting a digital sourcing mindset and inspiring continuous improvement within the team.\n\nAlso, you are fluent in both, written and spoken English.\n\nAbout The Department\n\nCorporate Procurement is responsible for the global indirect spend in Novo Nordisk of app. 35 billion DKK. We define and drive the global procurement strategy. With 180 employees based in Denmark and more than 500 colleagues globally in procurement, we are a strategic partner in the execution of the company‚Äôs strategy.\n\nWe promote a global mind-set, dedication to business partnering and a relentless focus on creating rewarding careers for our people. We invest significant resources in developing our employees and focus on high performance, fun and trust our people to make them thrive in their job every day! We believe that a non-hierarchical, empowered organisation, where you work with great colleagues, is the foundation for success ‚Äì for you and Novo Nordisk.\n\nWorking at Novo Nordisk\n\nNovo Nordisk is a leading global healthcare company with a 100-year legacy of driving change to defeat serious chronic diseases. Building on our strong legacy within diabetes, we are growing massively and expanding our commitment, reaching millions around the world and impacting more than 40 million patient lives daily. All of this has made us one of the 20 most valuable companies in the world by market cap. Our success relies on the joint potential and collaboration of our more than 72,000 employees around the world.\n\nContact \n\nFor further information, please contact Thomas Miskow, +45 3444 7893\n\nDeadline\n\n30 June 2025\n\nYou do not need to attach a cover letter to your application, but please include a few sentences about why you are applying in your resume or CV.\n\nTo ensure an efficient and fair recruitment process, please refrain from adding a photo in your CV.\n\nPlease note that only