kningsst√∏tte, som omfatter b√•de IT-kriminalteknik (ITK) samt Kriminalteknisk St√∏tte (KTS). Sektionen h√∏rer organisatorisk under Efterforskningslinjen i afdelingen for Personfarlig Kriminalitet.\n\nSektionen er geografisk placeret p√• Station Nord i Helsing√∏r og best√•r i dag af en sektionsleder, to fagkoordinatorer og 11 specialiserede medarbejdere. ITK udg√∏r heraf √©n fagkoordinator og syv medarbejdere fordelt p√• fire politiuddannede og tre civile\n\nIT-teknikere.\n\nOpgaven\n\nDin rolle indeb√¶rer at forene teknisk ekspertise med efterforskningens kompleksitet. Du vil v√¶re ansvarlig for at fx ekstrahere afg√∏rende beviser, kortl√¶gge personnetv√¶rk og gennemg√• slettede data, som potentielt kan v√¶re afg√∏rende for at opklare sager og sikre procesretf√¶rdighed for de involverede parter i et t√¶t makkerskab med dygtige efterforskere.\n\nDine daglige opgaver bliver i t√¶t dialog med efterforskere bl.a.\n\nÔÉò At gennemf√∏re digital efterforskning p√• sikret data.\n\nÔÉò At identificere digitale spor og beviser.\n\nÔÉò At analysere datas√¶t for at afd√¶kke m√∏nstre og relationer.\n\nÔÉò At udarbejde rapporter og dokumentation af digitale beviser.\n\nÔÉò At bidrage med din viden til at finde nye og smarte m√•der at l√∏se opgaverne p√•.\n\nTjenestestedet er Helsing√∏r Politistation, men der kan forekomme arbejde p√• de √∏vrige politistationer i Nordsj√¶llands Politi.\n\nDu kan ogs√• blive indkaldt som ekspertvidne i retten. For at g√∏re dig tryg i den rolle, f√•r du b√•de introduktion til og undervisning i at vidne i retten.\n\nDin ans√¶ttelse vil indeb√¶re et intensivt kursusforl√∏b, for at give dig den n√∏dvendige tr√¶ning og viden i at anvende de specialiserede softwarev√¶rkt√∏jer der benyttes samt forberede dig p√• de udfordringer du kan m√∏de i dit arbejde som IT-kriminaltekniker hos Nordsj√¶llands Politi. Vores m√•l er at sikre, at du er godt rustet til at h√•ndtere de daglige opgaver.\n\nDer kan planl√¶gges for kurser b√•de i indland som udland.\n\nDen normale tjeneste foreg√•r p√• hverdage i dagtimerne. I tilf√¶lde af alvorlige h√¶ndelser forventes det dog, at alle bidrager ud over den normale arbejdstid. Der l√¶gges derfor v√¶gt p√• fleksibilitet, herunder b√•de mulighed for og villighed til i perioder at p√•tage sig overarbejde samt kunne m√∏de ind ved tilkald uden for normal arbejdstid og i weekender.\n\nOm dig\n\nDu har en bred IT-teknisk profil med en st√¶rk analytisk tankegang, gerne kombineret med en videreg√•ende IT-uddannelse. Du har erfaring med databaser og har st√¶rke analytiske kompetencer og du evner at skabe overblik og struktur i st√∏rre datam√¶ngder.\n\nDet vil v√¶re en fordel, hvis du har stiftet bekendtskab med et eller flere af f√∏lgende programmeringssprog: Python, Bash, C#, Javascript eller lignende. Dette er dog ikke et krav.\n\nDu t√¶nker nyt, kreativt og ud af boksen. Da du br√¶nder for at s√¶tte dig ind i ny viden, holder du dig naturligt opdateret p√• de nyeste teknologier og programmer.\n\nDu trives i et milj√∏, hvor du selvst√¶ndigt tilrettel√¶gger arbejdet, og hvor du selv er ops√∏gende i forhold til sparring, ledelse og nye opgaver. Du trives derudover med at skulle dokumentere dine l√∏sninger, og du kommer til at indg√• i et engageret og fagligt st√¶rkt team, som du er med til at s√¶tte dit pr√¶g p√•.\n\nDu fremtr√¶der roligt og t√•lmodigt, bevarer overblikket og l√∏ser opgaverne ‚Äì ogs√• i pressede og stressede situationer. Du har humor og g√∏r meget for at skabe en positiv atmosf√¶re og et behageligt milj√∏ sammen med dine kollegaer.\n\nDu udviser parathed til at g√∏re tingene p√• nye m√•der, s√• l√¶nge at det g√∏res korrekt i forhold til de standarder som er g√¶ldende.\n\nL√∏n- og ans√¶ttelsesvilk√•r\n\nDu bliver ansat i henhold til relevant overenskomst\n\nHar du en akademisk baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til de til enhver tid g√¶ldende aftaler mellem Finansministeriet og Akademikernes Centralorganisation.\n\nHar du en anden uddannelsesm√¶ssig baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til den til enhver tid g√¶ldende organisationsaftale for kontorfunktion√¶rer i staten mellem Finansministeriet og HK/STAT samt OAO-S-f√¶llesoverenskomst.\n\nArbejdstiden er p√• 37 timer ugentligt.\n\nDet er en foruds√¶tning for ans√¶ttelse, at du kan sikkerhedsgodkendes til HEMMELIG, og at denne kan opretholdes under hele ans√¶ttelsen.\n\nDet er yderligere en foruds√¶tning at du har k√∏rekort til personbil ‚Äì kategori B.\n\nKontakt og ans√∏gning\n\nHar du sp√∏rgsm√•l til stillingen er du velkommen til at kontakte sektionsleder, politikommiss√¶r Rolf Kragh-Hoffmann, tlf. 51721073 / mail: rkh002@politi.dk.\n\nVi opfordrer alle interesserede til at s√∏ge, uanset alder, k√∏n, religion eller etnisk tilh√∏rsforhold.\n\nAns√∏gningsfrist: 6. juli 2025\n\nOm Nordsj√¶llands Politi\n\nI Nordsj√¶llands Politi er vi cirka 1.000 kollegaer, der m√∏der p√• arbejde i henholdsvis Helsing√∏r, Hiller√∏d, Birker√∏d, Gentofte og Frederikssund for at skabe tryghed, sikkerhed, fred og orden for borgerne i Nordsj√¶lland. Vi s√∏ger kollegaer, der vil v√¶re en del af en moderne og innovativ offentlig virksomhed, der l√∏ser opgaverne med h√∏j kvalitet. Det sigter vi mod ved blandt andet at inddrage og samarbejde med b√•de kredsens borgere samt den resterende del af samfundet i form af for eksempel kommuner, boligomr√•der og interesseorganisationer. Du kan l√¶se mere om Nordsj√¶llands Politi p√• www.politi.dk samt p√• Facebook og Twitter.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4253715935/','2025-06-23',NULL,NULL,'[\"Bash\", \"Linux\", \"SQL\", \"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"Databaser\", \"Efterforskning\", \"IT-serviceadministration\", \"ITIL\", \"Parathed\", \"Teknisk support\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:06:38','2025-06-30 14:06:38'),(100,4259459536,'ESG Finance Controller (Internal Finance)',58,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nWith more than 3,000 employees, Deloitte is the largest audit and consultancy firm in Denmark. We tailor solutions across Audit, Tax, Financial Advisory Services, Enterprise Risk Services, Technology and Transformations.\n\n\n\n\n\nJob Description\n\n\n\nAs a leading professional services firm with a global presence, we are dedicated to making an impact that matters. Our team in Denmark is committed to providing innovative solutions and exceptional service to our clients.\n\n\n\nWe pride ourselves on fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace where your unique talents are valued. Continuous learning and career growth are at the heart of our culture, empowering you to thrive both personally and professionally.\n\n\n\nAre you skilled in managing complex datasets with an audit mindset, passionate about sustainability and eager to make a significant impact in the world of ESG reporting? Deloitte is seeking a proactive and ambitious ESG Finance Controller to join our Internal Finance department (non-client facing) within the Compliance team in Copenhagen. This role is perfect for someone early in their career, with 2-5 years of relevant experience, ideally with a background in Audit & Assurance. Whether you\'ve already taken steps towards ESG or are deeply passionate about the topic, we want to hear from you!\n\n\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\n\n\nPioneering Role: Be at the forefront of driving the implementation of the Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive (CSRD) and ESG Reporting within Deloitte. Your work will ensure our firm remains at the forefront of sustainability and compliance excellence.\n\n\n\nCareer Growth: This position is not just a job; it is a steppingstone. As you develop, you\'ll gain increasing responsibility over the ESG reporting agenda, paving the way for your professional future within Deloitte.\n\n\n\nDynamic Environment: Thrive in a supportive and dynamic environment that encourages innovation and growth. You\'ll have the opportunity to collaborate with industry experts and contribute to meaningful change.\n\n\n\nIn this role, you will make an impact by:\n\n\n\nIntegrating CSRD Requirements: Playing a key role in incorporating CSRD standards into Deloitte\'s frameworks, ensuring comprehensive compliance and seamless reporting processes.\nPreparing Internal & External ESG Reporting: Compiling detailed ESG reports using complex datasets from multiple sources, ensuring accuracy and timeliness in disclosures to stakeholders.\nDeveloping Accounting Policies and Controls: Collaborating with the rest of the Compliance team to refine accounting policies and internal controls, enhancing ESG practices and standards.\nCollaborating Across Borders: Partnering with internal, regional and global stakeholders to align ESG initiatives with corporate objectives, ensuring consistent adherence to regulatory mandates.\nKeeping Up to Date: Keeping abreast of industry trends and regulatory changes, proactively adapting strategies to align with best practices.\nAutomating and Improving Processes: Identifying opportunities to automate and improve ESG reporting processes for enhanced efficiency.\nFacilitating Training: Organizing training sessions to elevate organizational understanding and implementation of ESG policies and practices.\n\n\nQualifications\n\n\n\nTo excel in this role, you should possess the following qualifications and skills:\n\n\n\nA degree with a strong academic track record in Accounting, Finance or Economics (ideally CMA / HD).\nA minimum of two years of relevant experience within ESG, sustainability, compliance, assurance, or internal controls - preferably from an international organization.\nAbility to understand and comply with reporting standards: ESRS, IFRS, etc.\nCuriosity to understand business requirements and a passion for improving processes.\nA diligent and analytical mindset that can provide insights from complex data.\nProficiency in Microsoft Office Suite; SAP experience is a plus.\nStrong problem-solving skills and the ability to collaborate effectively with stakeholders on developing new processes.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, with fluency in English being a requirement.\n\nEven if you do not see yourself in all the bullets above, we still encourage you to apply if you believe your skills can make an impact on our team.\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\n\n\n\nThe Compliance team at Deloitte Copenhagen is a dedicated group of professionals committed to ensuring the firm‚Äôs adherence to regulatory requirements, including the Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive (CSRD). This close-knit team currently consists of five members: four full-time employees and one student analyst, each bringing a unique set of skills and perspectives to the table.\n\n\n\nLed by Alexandru Ancateu, the team works collaboratively to maintain Deloitte‚Äôs compliance with evolving regulatory standards. Alexandru can be reached at +45 30 93 41 25 for any inquiries related to the team‚Äôs activities or specific questions regarding the ESG Finance Controller position.\n\n\n\nThe Compliance team is part of the broader Operational Finance department within Finance and plays a crucial role in maintaining Deloitte‚Äôs reputation for excellence and integrity, working diligently to align our practices with evolving regulatory standards. Joining this team means becoming part of a dynamic group committed to making a meaningful impact within the organization and the broader community.\n\n\n\nWhat We Offer\n\n\n\nAt Deloitte, you will be an essential part of our exciting journey within Finance, working in an inclusive and diverse culture that values authenticity and encourages leadership at all levels. We foster an environment where you can bring your unique experiences and ideas to work, making a real impact within our organization. Deloitte provides a challenging and rewarding job with ample opportunities for personal and professional development.\n\n\n\nIf you\'re ready to embark on a rewarding career journey with Deloitte, where your efforts will drive sustainability and compliance excellence, apply today. Together, we can shape the future of ESG reporting and make a lasting impact.\n\n\n\nDo you want to be part of our team? Click the \"I am interested\" button above if you are ready to join our team. Send your application, CV and grade transcript from your most recent education as well as other relevant documents. We process applications and arrange interviews continually, so we recommend that you apply as soon as possible.\n\n\n\nApplication date: As soon as 18.07.2025 Expected start date: 01.09.2025\n\n\n\nWe encourage all candidates to apply for the position regardless of, e.g., age, gender (gender identity and gender expression), sexual orientation, religion, ethnicity, nationality, or disability.\n\n\n\nBy applying for this job, you will be assessed against the Deloitte Global Talent Standards. We have designed these standards to provide a consistent and exceptional Deloitte employee experience globally.\n\n\n\nWe look forward to connecting with you!\n\n\n\nIn Deloitte, you will find passionate, caring people who are curious by nature and striving to evolve. We value our different skills, perspectives and experiences and foster an environment where innovative powers thrive. To us, success is the feeling that the work we are doing will outlast us. The impact we make is not about what we achieve as individuals, but how we enable those around us to be their very best. From professional development to leadership opportunities, we empower our people to be extraordinary by playing to their strengths ‚Äì because that is how we can make a difference.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259459536/','2025-06-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Engelsk\", \"Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG)\", \"Finansiel rapportering\", \"Intern kontrol\", \"Kommunikation\", \"Kontoafstemning\", \"Likviditet\", \"Microsoft Excel\", \"Oral Communication\", \"Probleml√∏sning\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:07:19','2025-06-30 14:07:19'),(101,4259434435,'Experienced Automation Engineers Pipeline for Greater Copenhagen Area',2,'Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you ready to take the next step and pursue a life-changing career at Novo Nordisk? Are you driven by automation and digitalization of the Novo Nordisk manufacturing value chain? Look no further!\n\nWe are building a talent pipeline for skilled and innovative automation engineers to join Novo Nordisk in shaping the future through automation.\n\nJoining the Automation Engineers Pipeline\nBy applying for the pipeline, you will be considered as a potential match for on-site automation related positions, which align with your background, skills, and interests across various areas in Denmark.\n\nWe‚Äôll match your profile proactively with relevant positions. Once a Hiring Manager shows interest in your profile, the Hiring Manager Team will reach out to you and tell you more about the current position and invite you for the 1st Interview.\n\nLocations\nWe are looking for candidates to all our locations. This specific pipeline covers on-site positions in Greater Copenhagen area e.g.: Bagsv√¶rd, Gentofte, S√∏borg, Lyngby, M√•l√∏v, Kirke V√¶rl√∏se.\n\nWe look forward to receiving your application and to having the opportunity to provide a solid match for open positions.\n\nAbout The Positions\n\nDue to the expansion of our activities in all business areas and sites, we are currently seeking talents for many different teams across Novo Nordisk, such as Advanced automation, Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES), and Collaborative- and industrial robotics. We encourage you to read more detailed information about the different roles and areas through this link: Automation engineers and process digitalization (novonordisk.com)\n\nQualifications\n\nWe are looking for someone with an innovative and solution-oriented mindset. As you will be working and collaborating with people from various departments in the organization, it would be preferable that you are ready to take the lead on deploying solutions that bring value.\n\nIn addition, you have the following qualifications:\n\n\n\nBachelor‚Äôs or master‚Äôs degree in Automation, IT, Autonomous systems, Robotics, or another related field\nStrong knowledge of IT/OT\nA technical background and/or experience within engineering, IT/OT, digitalization and automation\nFluent in English both oral and written. Danish is a great advantage.\n\n\n\n\nTechnical skills/knowledge:\n\n\n\nAdvanced automation e.g.: (PLC, SCADA, DeltaV, ABB SattLine/800xA)\nManufacturing Execution Systems e.g.: (PAS-X or Syncade)\nCollaborative- and mobile robotics e.g.: (Universal Robots, Kuka, MIR, Omron, Nipper).\n\n\n\n\nAs documentation according to Good Manufacturing Practice (GMP), rules are part of our daily work, it is important that you thrive in ensuring that all your work is well documented.\n\nWe also welcome and encourage early talent to apply for our pipelines, as we are committed to fostering growth and development in our employees and providing opportunities for long-term career success. Please make sure to apply to this https://careers.novonordisk.com/job-invite/328808/\n\nCheck list when applying\n\n\nWhen choosing your privacy settings, please select: ‚ÄúProfile Visibility: Novo Nordisk Recruiter Worldwide‚Äù.\nYou do not need to attach a cover letter to your application, and please make sure to delete previous cover letters from your profile.\nWe encourage you to include a few sentences about why you are interested in the position in your CV.\nTo ensure an efficient and fair recruitment process, please refrain from adding a photo to your CV.\nMake sure to apply to each location that you are interested in separately. For example, if you want to work in Kalundborg or Hiller√∏d, you need to apply to both the Kalundborg and Hiller√∏d pipeline job post.\nWe kindly ask you to withdraw your application if you are no longer interested.\n\n\n\n\nThe pipeline is open for applications until 02.10.2025. Due to GDPR we close the pipelines after 6 months and send email notifications to all active candidates when they are closed, with a link to where you can re-apply to our new Engineers Pipeline.\n\nWe commit to an inclusive recruitment process and equality of opportunity for all our job applicants.\n\nAt Novo Nordisk we recognize that it is no longer good enough to aspire to be the best company in the world. We need to aspire to be the best company for the world and we know that this is only possible with talented employees with diverse perspectives, backgrounds and cultures. We are therefore committed to creating an inclusive culture that celebrates the diversity of our employees, the patients we serve and communities we operate in. Together, we‚Äôre life changing.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259434435/','2025-06-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Automatisering\", \"Python\", \"Elektromekanik\", \"Fejlfinding\", \"Instrumentering\", \"MES\", \"PLC\", \"PLC-programmering\", \"Robotteknik\", \"SCADA\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:07:19','2025-06-30 14:07:19'),(102,4259422902,'Medhj√¶lper under 18 √•r til bageriet - Ballerup',21,'Ballerup, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nMedhj√¶lper under 18 √•r til bageriet\n\nVil du v√¶re en del af et team af sjove og dygtige kolleger, og vil du have et studiejob, hvor du kan tjene lidt ekstra og samtidig l√¶re om detailbranchen?\n\nDet er sikkert allerede nok for dig, men du f√•r ogs√• vigtig erhvervserfaring til CV‚Äôet. Erfaring, der hj√¶lper dig, n√•r du engang skal videre eller tage dit n√¶ste skridt hos os. Og s√• bliver du ansat under ordnede forhold ‚Äì og det er vi stolte af.\n\nBliv en del af sammenholdet i f√∏tex \n\nHos f√∏tex deler vi en vinder√•nd og en stolthed over at g√∏re det hele lidt mere l√¶kkert. Vi er sammen om at give kunderne en ekstra god service og tilbyde de bedste varer i en indbydende butik med h√∏jt til loftet. Vi er dog ikke st√∏rre end, at alle kender alle, s√• du kan se frem til at blive en d