bet\n\nAre you passionate about advanced graphics and software development? With us, you‚Äôll get the chance to work with cutting-edge technologies like Vulkan in a cloud-based setup ‚Äì and leave your mark on everything from architecture to new features. Step into a role where your ideas aren‚Äôt just heard ‚Äì they become part of the product.\n\nYour new role\n\nAs an experienced computer graphics developer, we expect you will take responsibility for implementing tasks of medium to high complexity, actively contributing to our software architecture and cross-team collaborations. Depending on your experiences and interests, you will build new features for our existing platform, and drive and contribute to new initiatives that can take our software development processes to new and greater heights.\n\nAdditionally, you will‚Ä¶\n\n\n Own your tasks from beginning to end, including partaking in the design of the solution with our Product design team and Product managers ‚Äì because who knows, maybe your idea is better? We‚Äôd like to know! \n Assist in improving our architecture and the reduction of technical debt \n Bring new ideas to the table to help us improve ‚Äì either through code, processes or something entirely different! \n\n\nOur tech\n\nBuilt on a distributed cloud system, our computer graphics software consists of C#, OpenGL and Vulkan.\n\nWe aim to offer our customers and users new features and an improved product continuously, and in order to meet this goal, the development is characterized by agile methodologies and loosely defined time estimates, with approximately six annual releases.\n\nYour background\n\nWe believe you...\n\n\n Have strong experience in Software Development (experience with C# and Vulkan). \n Have a solid theoretical foundation from a bachelor‚Äôs degree in computer science, engineering, IT or similar. \n Understand the hardware you‚Äôre programming to, as well as the performance bottlenecks and limitations when programming for mult