j√∏videnskab\", \"Probleml√∏sning\", \"Project engineering\", \"Projektplanl√¶gning\", \"R√•dgivning\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:11:02','2025-06-30 14:11:02'),(138,4228267061,'Senior Backend Engineer',66,'K√∏benhavn og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nAt Famly, we‚Äôre looking for a Senior Backend Engineer to build awesome GraphQL and REST APIs to enable our platform to help the thousands of daycares that use Famly.\n\nAnd who are Famly? We‚Äôre on a mission to close the collaboration gap in early childhood. So we‚Äôre building the world‚Äôs most collaborative Early Childhood Platform - a software platform for the adults in a young child‚Äôs life to connect, share their workload, and learn about early childhood. Basically, Famly makes life easier for educators and families so that they can get back to what matters.\n\nAs a Senior Backend Engineer, we expect you to have at least 3-4 years of experience with Backend technologies.\n\nWe are looking for people to join us at our Copenhagen headquarters, located in K√∏bmagergade in the centre of the city or at our office in Berlin.\n\n\n\n\nWhat you\'ll be doing:\n\nWorking in one of our crews with other Frontenders, Backenders, a Designer, a Product manager and an Engineering manager.\nYou will play a key role in planning what‚Äôs next, designing, developing and rolling out cool new features and changes.\nYou‚Äôll team up with the Backend Chapter to shape the future of our tech stack, tooling and reducing complexity across our code.\n\n\n\n\nYou‚Äôll thrive in this role if you can:\n\nBuild solid APIs in GraphQL and REST (we primarily use Scala with our GraphQL API but also maintain a PHP REST API)\nUse Scala and functional programming (we use Cats, Cats-effect, FS2, Refined, and Slick), or have a strong desire to learn it.\nModel complex data structures and express them in a relational way (we use MySQL)\nBring crystal clarity to complex and ambiguous ideas and projects.\nCommunicate feedback, expectations and information in clear and kind ways, both written and spoken (we‚Äôre over 40 different nationalities, and our company language is English)\nLearn super fast, be open-minded and ready to adapt our technology, teams and ways-of-working as Famly scales in brave new directions.\nMake your teammates shine by supporting each other to learn and grow.\n\n\n\n\nWhile we‚Äôd love someone who has experience in the arena doing this type of work, we appreciate that everyone brings something unique. If you don‚Äôt tick every box above, to hell with it - apply anyway. We‚Äôd still love to read your application.\n\n\n\n\nThe interview process looks like:\n\nAn intro video chat with our People Partner\nLogical test\nTake-home technical assignment with a follow-up chat\nPersonal interview\n\n\n\n\nAnd who are Famly?\n\nYou‚Äôre probably wondering at this stage, and Famly are...? Well, it all began when our co-founder Henrik‚Äôs daughter was ready to start at daycare. He couldn‚Äôt believe the amount of work being done on paper - and how distant he felt from his first child during the day. The paper ‚Äòparent‚Äô books they exchanged once a month just weren‚Äôt cutting it. Together with his friend, our co-founder and CEO Anders, they set about solving that.\n\nThese days, the 180 of us building Famly talk about trying to do one thing. Giving children the best possible start to life. Or rather, making it easier for the 8,000 nurseries and childcare centers who use Famly every day to that, on our behalf.\n\nWe do it with the world‚Äôs first Early Childhood Platform, software that brings hundreds of thousands of parents closer to their child‚Äôs day while they‚Äôre away from them. We also make financial, pedagogical, and planning tools for more than 100,000 childcare professionals in the UK, US, Germany and 15 other countries, saving them hours and reducing their admin stress.\n\nUltimately, that gives them more time and headspace for the little ones that really matter.\n\n\n\n\nYou‚Äôll love working here because