ng the integration and optimization of OT systems within manufacturing processes. You will contribute to building innovative MI and data collection solutions tailored to organizational needs. Additionally, mentoring junior colleagues and driving strategic initiatives for MI and OT technology adoption will be central to your role.\n\nYour main tasks are:\n\n\n\nPerforming systematic on-site testing and evaluation of MI and OT systems.\nDefining Engineering Specifications (ES) for MI solutions.\nAssisting in the definition of IT architecture for data collection and test plans for MI systems while executing them effectively.\nEnsuring compliance with GMP regulations through the development and review of relevant documentation (e.g., IFA, ITRA, DS, O&M).\n\n\n\n\nThis is an opportunity to explore new technology and inspire production areas across Novo Nordisk to automate their processes. The position covers a high level of complexity, and the daily work requires interaction with a wide range of stakeholders (online, or in person at the office).\n\nQualifications\n\nTo be considered for this role, we imagine you have:\n\n\n\nBachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs degree within Engineering or another relevant field. \nSome experience or technical background within Manufacturing Intelligence and OT systems.\nIf you do not have a visible physical disability, we ask you to refrain applying to this position.\n\n\n\n\nWe strongly encourage you to apply even if you are new to Manufacturing Intelligence field and are eager to learn and grow in a dynamic environment.\n\nAbout Our Office Space\n\nThe office space is flexible seating, however there is an option for a fixed desk for our new colleague and potentially also for a personal assistant who accompanies you. If there are other needs or requirements necessary, we will try to accommodate them in cooperation with you and, it will be possible to apply for assistive devices performing the tasks.\n\nAbout The Department\n\nThe position is loc