 of the projects vary according to ongoing activities across PS AMSAT and will be matched with your educational background and competencies. \n\nThe practicalities\n\n\n\nIt is a normal permanent full-time position. When approaching the end of the rotations, we will support you in transferring to your future position in PS AMSAT depending on your competences, business needs, and development wishes \nStart date: 2 February 2026 \n\n\n\n\nQualifications \n\nWe expect that: \n\n\n\nYou are newly graduated or about to graduate with a master‚Äôs degree level or similar within a relevant life science education \nYou may have experience from the pharmaceutical industry via your studies or student job \nYou are proactive with a strong focus on learning, open-minded and very curious by nature \nYou are good at communicating and collaborating with stakeholders at all levels across a global organisation \nYou are analytical and able to structure and cope with a lot of information and varied tasks \nYou possess strong intercultural skills and are fluent in both spoken and written English \n\n\n\n\nInformation sessions \n\nAre you interested in learning more about this exciting opportunity? We invite you to join us for an information session where you will receive an introduction to Novo Nordisk, PS AMSAT, and our Development Academy.\n\nWe will also have one of our graduates joining the session, providing you with first-hand insights and the chance to have your questions answered directly by someone currently enrolled in the programme.\n\nWe will host 3 options:\n\n\n\nThursday 12-Jun-2025, 2:30 PM - 3:15 PM (CET): LINK \nMonday 25-Aug-2025, 8:30 AM - 9:15 AM (CET): LINK \nTuesday 26-Aug-2025, 4:00 PM - 4:45 PM (CET): LINK \n\n\n\n\nDeadline \n\nPlease submit your application (Motivation & CV ‚Äì short motivation can be included in CV) no later than 29-August-2025\n\nContact \n\nFor further information, check-in at our webinars or contact Manager, Jonas Andersen Helboe‚ÄØat +45 30 79 49 52 \n\nRecruitment process \n\nStep 1 ‚Äì mid September: Relevant candidates will be invited for an initial online interview. The candidates who are not invited for an interview will be notified by e-mail. \n\nStep 2 ‚Äì end September: Shortlisted candidates will receive an event invite for 07-October-2025, where they will take part in assessment day and get a chance to learn more about the Development Academy & Novo Nordisk.‚ÄØThe event will take place in Bagsv√¶rd, Denmark and will be arranged by Novo Nordisk.\n\nStep 3 ‚Äì beginning October: The final group of candidates will be invited for individual interviews where a case presentation is part of the interview.\n\nStep 4 ‚Äì November: Recruitment is finalised, and final decisions will be communicated to candidates.\n\nWe commit to an inclusive recruitment process and equality of opportunity for all our job applicants.\n\nAt Novo Nordisk we recognize that it is no longer good enough to aspire to be the best company in the world. We need to aspire to be the best company for the world and we know that this is only possible with talented employees with diverse perspectives, backgrounds and cultures. We are therefore committed to creating an inclusive culture that celebrates the diversity of our employees, the patients we serve and communities we operate in. Together, we‚Äôre life changing.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259436224/','2025-06-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Engelsk\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"Case Presentation\", \"GMP\", \"Injektioner\", \"Interkulturelle f√¶rdigheder\", \"Pharmaceutical Manufacturing\", \"Produktionsprocesser\", \"Videnskabelig uddannelse\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:13:19','2025-06-30 14:13:19'),(158,4243592503,'Software Engineer',73,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nSoftware Engineer og Azure udvikler \n\n\n\n\nHar du evnen og interessen for at pr√∏ve kr√¶fter med udvikling af komplekse Azure cloud-l√∏sninger? cVation s√∏ger erfarne